hackeray Ritchie: Journals and letters|date=1994|publisher=Ohio State Univ. Press|location=Columbus|isbn=9780814206386|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=SHnxiQMZKhwC|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|last1=G\u00e9rin|first1=Winifred|title=Anne Thackeray Ritchie: a biography|date=1981|publisher=Oxford U.P.|location=Oxford|isbn=9780198126645|url=https://books.google.com/books?redir_esc=y&id=UDZbAAAAMAAJ|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book| last = Garnett| first = Henrietta| title = Anny: A Life of Anny Thackeray Ritchie| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=t6cca0xnAKMC|year = 2004| publisher = [[Chatto & Windus]]|location=London| isbn = 0-7011-7129-4 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|d=Q740657|s=author:Leslie Stephen|commons=category:Leslie Stephen|n=no|b=no|v=no|voy=no|mw=no|m=no|species=no|wikt=no}}\n\n* {{Gutenberg author |id=Stephen,+Leslie | name=Leslie Stephen}}\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Leslie Stephen |sopt=t}}\n* {{Librivox author |id=1188}}\n* [https://archive.org/details/historyenglisht06stepgoog History of English Thought in the Eighteenth Century] at [[Internet Archive]].\n* [http://archive.spectator.co.uk/article/27th-february-1904/9/i-n-sir-leslie-stephen-we-have-lost-one-of-the Obituary]\n* [https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/5618/leslie-stephen Grave]\n\n=== External images ===\n* [http://www.smith.edu/libraries/libs/rarebook/exhibitions/stephen/35d.htm Leslie and Harriet Stephen 1867], in {{harvtxt|Kukil|2011}}\n* [http://www.smith.edu/libraries/libs/rarebook/exhibitions/stephen/31a.htm Julia Prinsep Jackson, c.1856],  in {{harvtxt|Kukil|2011}}\n\n{{Virginia Woolf|state=collapsed}}\n{{FBA 1902}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stephen, Leslie}}\n[[Category:1832 births]]\n[[Category:1904 deaths]]\n[[Category:English mountain climbers]]\n[[Category:English biographers]]\n[[Category:Dictionary of National Biography]]\n[[Category:People educated at Eton College]]\n[[Category:Stephen-Bell family]]\n[[Category:English agnostics]]\n[